entries.femaleVariant: Saw a weird image in town.
Saw a weird image out on the street. Seems like your line of work.
entries.maleVariant: I saw a weird image out on the street. Uhh, seems like your line of work.

entries.femaleVariant: Grabbed a scan, take a look.
Tarot, major arcanum. What you saw was a sign from a higher power!
Either gone completely whacked, or I'm havin' a mystical moment.
So – saw a weird mural on the wall.
Listen, don't laugh, but – been seein' some weird shit around town. Like, murals or somethin'. But know they're not real.
entries.maleVariant: Listen, don't laugh, uh, but – been seein' some weird shit around town. Like, murals or somethin'. But I know they're not real.

entries.femaleVariant: Eh, just a Kiroshi blip. Could take a look.
That case, it's the biochip. Brain can't handle the data overload. Either that, or it's reached the cortex.
Can you do anything?
No, no, the images are too complex for a blip. It's like they're – symbols.
Nope. Better find a way to get rid of that chip.
Misty? Eh, more likely a neuron misfire for Viktor to check out... Or maybe I ask 'em both.
What'd it look like?
Higher power could be a little clearer.
Major arcanum? What's that?
The-- the what now? Major arcanum?
Tarot card, archetype, knowledge held in symbolic form, a stage in your journey through life – take your pick.
Either way – you're sayin' some higher power's talkin' to me through tarot cards?
Or to Silverhand. Or both of you, seeing as you form a harmonious whole at the moment.
Be a little easier if this higher power learned to be direct.
Well, the world is a maze of illusions. It's not easy for the light to shine into the prison of our earthly existence.
Right, great – so what do I do with a sign I can't understand, from a power I know nothing about?
entries.maleVariant: Right, great – so what do I do with a sign I can't understand, from a power I know nothin' about?

entries.femaleVariant: I'd start by looking for more of them. The tarot describes a road – so go down it.
Nope. Not buying it.
What do I do with what I find?
Nope. Don't buy it. Sorry, mystical messages from the beyond are, uh, beyond me.
Still don't know what I'm s'posed to do with what I find.
Well, if I were you, I wouldn't ignore the signs.
Look for more images. They must have some connection to the place where you find them.
Think about what you see. You ask me, they've been sent to help you find the truth.
Ugh, findin' the truth is pretty far down on my list at the moment.
entries.maleVariant: Findin' the truth is pretty far down on my list at the moment.

entries.femaleVariant: A difficult time is coming when you'll have to choose which road to take. Then, you'll understand.
Come on back when you've found more. I'll help you decipher what you've seen.
Dunno...
What's that chick's name, the one with the hair?
Hey, look!
Would ya look at that. You see it too, right?
Huh, interesting.
Well, well, well...
Who woulda thought...
What do we have here?
